intent_execution_notes:
intent_execution_notes: {
  intent_1: "Worn over fitted close/tight bottom. Body engaged throughout, deep V reinforces vertical line through the upper body, lace trim provides feminine accent without breaking the column. Waist-length hem ends at the natural waist but isn't a styling event when worn untucked. The result is a fitted vertical silhouette with featured upper body (décolletage, bust).",

intent_2: "Half-tucked or fully tucked into a high-rise bottom — the waist-length cut permits a clean tuck. The skim-fit cotton + tuck + visible high waistband makes a crisp waist at the meeting point; close-top read, so the transition is sharp rather than bloused. styling_anchor strategy: she creates the waist with the tuck, while the deep V keeps the décolletage as the upper feature and the meeting point becomes the waist below. Strong Intent 2 for hourglass (shape confirmed) and for any tucker who wants a crisp waist. Untucked it traces instead (Intent 1) — her choice."

