intent_execution_notes:
intent_execution_notes: {
  intent_7: "Co-ord set with styling_flexibility: open — supports multiple wearing modes. The set can be worn together (matching coordinated look), split apart (oversized top with denim, shorts with a different tank), tucked vs untucked depending on user preference. Fires for multi-modal users who run different silhouettes day-to-day and value pieces that flex across modes rather than committing to a single silhouette.",

  intent_9: "Body covered by oversized top through torso; deliberate design opening at mid-thigh hem reveals legs as the visual event. Loose garment + body disengagement on top + structured leg opening = textbook Intent 9 pattern. The mid-thigh exposure is the designed discontinuity that draws the eye, parallel to how deep V necklines feature décolletage or asymmetric hems feature back. Fires for users who named legs as featuring zone + are exposure-comfortable with legs + prefer the cover-and-open-strategically register over the body-engaged register."
}

intent_execution_notes: {
  intent_2: "Worn with the polo tucked into the high-rise wide-leg trousers. The polo blouses over the elastic waistband creating the waist event at the meeting point — softer than a fitted-top tuck but the visual story of the outfit lands at the waist. styling_anchor strategy. Hourglass uses this to confirm her natural shape within the composed-contemporary register; rectangle uses it to create the waist event through the technique. The bloused effect is the design intent, not a compromise.",

  intent_6: "Worn with the polo untucked, falling past the waist over the wide-leg drape trousers. Body completely disengaged — drape covers torso, polo hides waist, wide-leg covers legs. Pure step-back composition in composed-contemporary register. neutral strategy.",

  intent_7: "Co-ord set with styling_flexibility: open — supports multiple wearing modes. The set can be worn together (matching coordinated look), split apart (polo with denim, trousers with a different top), tucked vs untucked depending on the user's daily preference. Multi-modal Intent 7 users get genuine flexibility from this set — it adapts to her styling choices rather than committing to one silhouette."
}

intent_execution_notes: {
  intent_1: "Worn over fitted close/tight bottom (or relaxed bottom for a softer read). Body engaged throughout via close ribbed knit + waist-length termination. No edge break, no styling event — the waist-length hem is just where the top ends, not a visual focal point. Clean vertical column with the ribbed texture as the design statement.",

  intent_2: "Half-tucked or fully tucked into high-rise bottom (slim jean, wide-leg, trouser). The fitted top + tuck + visible high waistband = clean waist event at the meeting point. styling_anchor strategy. Smoke-and-mirrors waist creation. The ribbed texture catches light at the meeting point, making the waist transition visible. Strong Intent 2 match for hourglass (natural shape confirmed) and for users who use the tuck to create the waist event."
}

intent_execution_notes: {
  intent_1: "Worn over fitted close/tight bottom (no — this IS the bottom). Worn with fitted top untucked falling at hip length over the extra-high waistband. The close fit through hip/seat + straight leg + cropped ankle delivers a body-traced column from natural waist to ankle. The cropped hem at ankle is at the smallest leg point — doesn't break vertical line.",

  intent_2: "Tucked into the extra-high waistband. The high rise sits above the natural waist creating a dramatic meeting point with the tucked fitted top. styling_anchor strategy at peak strength. The featuring_zones: seat element means the Cheeky butt-boosting cut adds visual interest at the seat as a secondary focal point, but the waist event remains the primary visual story for Intent 2 users."
}

