intent_execution_notes:
intent_execution_notes: {
  intent_1: "Worn with fitted top untucked over the high-rise waistband. The slim/cigarette cut + close fit through hip and leg + full length = body-traced column from natural waist to ankle. Strong Intent 1 match — the slim cut traces leg-line aggressively, delivering a clean vertical read with strong body engagement throughout.",

  intent_2: "Tucked into the high-rise waistband. The fitted seat + visible waistband + slim leg creates the strongest waist event in the catalog — the high rise meets the tucked fitted top at the natural waist, while the slim cut below keeps the silhouette body-traced throughout. styling_anchor strategy at peak effectiveness. Smoke-and-mirrors waist creation.",

  intent_5: "Worn with oversized or relaxed top untucked. The slim/cigarette cut + close fit reveals the leg-line as the visual event while the upper body is covered. Textbook Intent 5 — cover-on-top + body-tracing-bottom = legs as the focal redirect. The canonical slim leg-feature item; stronger Intent 5 match than straight-leg bottoms because the slim aggressively traces leg rather than just covering it."
}

intent_execution_notes: {
  intent_3: "The gathered seam at the natural waist creates a real garment-built waist event without requiring the user to tuck or belt. soft_anchor strategy through jersey gathering. The relaxed bodice falls from shoulders to the gathered waist; the A-line skirt drapes from the gathered waist to the midi hem. The user puts on the dress and the silhouette is constructed — soft waist suggestion + relaxed top + A-line below. Fires for users whose Q5b = yes (garment-defined waist). Works as a throw-on easy daily dress for users committed to garment-built silhouettes. Note: the construction creates a garment silhouette rather than displaying the body's silhouette — rectangle and inverted_triangle gain from the constructed shape; hourglass and triangle wear it without harm but their natural curves remain hidden under the drape."
}

